{"id":"259510036_Solving_the_density_classification_problem_with_a_large_diffusion_and_small_amplification_cellular_automaton","abstract":"One of the most studied inverse problems in cellular automata (CAs) is\nthe density classification problem. It consists in finding a CA such\nthat, given any initial configuration of 0s and 1s, it converges to the\nall-1 fixed point configuration if the fraction of 1s is greater than\nthe critical density 1/2, and it converges to the all-0 fixed point\nconfiguration otherwise. In this paper, we propose an original approach\nto solve this problem by designing a CA inspired by two mechanisms that\nare ubiquitous in nature: diffusion and nonlinear sigmoidal response.\nThis CA, which is different from the classical ones because it has many\nstates, has a success ratio of 100%, and works for any system size, any\ndimension, and any critical density.","authors":["Raimundo Briceño","Pablo Moisset de Espanés","Axel Osses","Ivan Rapaport"],"meta":["October 2013Physica D Nonlinear Phenomena 261:70-80","DOI:10.1016/j.physd.2013.07.002"],"references":["243775311_One-dimensional_Uniform_Arrays_that_Wash_out_Finite_Islands","228638548_Front_Propagation_in_Heterogeneous_Media","227186203_The_Gacs-Kurdyumov-Levin_automaton_revisited","221609662_A_white-box_DES_implementation_for_DRM_applications","2823852_Coevolving_the_Ideal_Trainer_Application_to_the_Discovery_of_Cellular_Automata_Rules","284307229_Coevolving_the_ideal_trainer_Application_to_the_discovery_of_cellular_automata_rules","262399637_Self-reproducing_automata","247602033_Spatial_Ecology_via_Reaction-Diffusion_Equations","237062593_Random_processes_and_transformations","233971724_Dynamic_Patterns_in_Complex_Systems","230994070_A_very_effective_density_classifier_two-dimensional_cellular_automaton_with_memory","228531619_Solving_the_Density_Classification_Task_Using_Cellular_Automaton_184_with_Memory","226397563_On_the_Cahn-Hilliard_equation","226211884_Lattice_Dynamical_Systems","2241